# ğŸŒ± Java CI/CD Beginner Project â€“ Step-by-Step Guide (Java 21)

This project demonstrates a simple Java 21 application and explains each step clearly to build, test, containerize, and automate it using Maven, Docker, Jenkins, and GitHub.

---

## ğŸ›  Prerequisites

- Java 21  
- Maven 3.x  
- Docker  
- Git  
- Jenkins (with Docker access)

Verify:
```bash
java --version
mvn --version
docker --version
git --version
```

---

## ğŸ“Œ Step 1: Create Project Folder

```bash
mkdir java-application
cd java-application
```

Why:  
Creates a root folder to keep Java, Maven, Docker, and Jenkins files together.

---

## ğŸ“Œ Step 2: Create Maven Directory Structure

```bash
mkdir -p src/main/java/com/message
mkdir -p src/test/java/com/message
```

Why:  
Maven requires this standard structure to identify application and test code.

